      "content": "Weathered planks creak beneath your feet as the dock juts out over grey-green water. Fishing boats knock gently against their moorings, their paint flaking in long pale strips. The smell of salt and tar hangs in the still air.\n\nTangled **fishing nets** hang from a post, drying in the salt breeze. Something might be caught in them.\n\nA cobbled road leads north toward the village, and a sandy path follows the shoreline east."
    },
